726278f-a.title: Queens: Brookhaven Avenue - Beach 19th Street
726278f-a.text:
Brookhaven Ave. (left), at the N.W. corner of Beach 19th Street,
showing the Sagamore Hotel formerly (1891) the Hotel Brunswick.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726279f-a.title: Queens: Brookhaven Avenue - Beach 19th Street
726279f-a.text:
Brookhaven Ave., at the S.E. corner of Beach 19th Street, showing
the Hotel Belvedere; known as the Foss Hotel from 1873 to 1891.
May 1923.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.
726279f-a.folder: Brookhaven Avenue & Beach 19th Street, Queens, NY

726833f-b.title: Queens: Greenport Road - Brookhaven Avenue
726833f-b.text:
Greenport Road, east side, north from Brookhaven to New Haven
Aves., showing in the center of the view what Eugene L. Armbruster
believes to be the former New York Hotel remodeled. (Note, do not
confuse this hotel with Lelia's New York Hotel as both have the
same title). It is now known as the Hotel Trouville. This is a set
oof two views. No. 2 shows the structure before it was remodeled.
May 1923.
View 2: About 1900.
Eucene L. Armbruster Collection.
726833f-b.folder: Greenport Road & Brookhaven Avenue, Queens, NY
